text: Two Ocean Beach surfers helped rescue a group of swimmers who were apparently caught in treacherous rip currents on Thursday afternoon at the south end of Ocean Beach in San Francisco. https://t.co/9SLDNrd2Qe

text: Coronavirus latest: Antibodies from people who recovered from SARS may be critical to fighting COVID-19, according to a recent study. https://t.co/gMUKr3C7M0

text: What is expected to be BART’s new fare gate of the future recently arrived at the Richmond station, where riders on Thursday said they doubted it would stop fare cheats even as the transit agency's Board of Directors praised the new device. https://t.co/kMaSXLMuqQ

text: San Francisco skaters "bomb hills" at Twin Peaks in a Skateboard Rally for Black Lives on Thursday. https://t.co/2zrnSLi3dN

text: Water in Lake Tahoe is nearly as murky as it’s been in 52 years of record-keeping, according to a new report from UC Davis. https://t.co/hGr7zVOls4

name: sfchronicle
text: The Oakland A’s selected Jeff Criswell, a right-hander from Michigan, with the 66th overall pick in the draft Thursday. Criswell’s dad, Brian, played in the Athletics’ organization. https://t.co/CScuDFyYUq

name: sfchronicle
text: After recent large demonstrations against racial injustice and police brutality, Bay Area health officials and experts have not said protesters need to automatically self-quarantine for coronavirus. But some recommend testing under certain circumstances. https://t.co/HTjvBN9Jgj

name: sfchronicle
text: 8,000 National Guard troops were deployed to cities across California, costing nearly $25 million, after some of the widespread protests against police violence and institutional racism turned chaotic. https://t.co/9Ftbg6mym1
